{title: On The Back Row}
{artist: George Jones}
{composer: written by Jerry Chestnut and Norris Wilson}

[C]Here I sit on the [F]back row in a [C]church down the street
Not to far from the [F]place where we used to [C]meet
And to find me getting [C7]though to me you [F]found someone to love
But [G7]I'll go back to the place that I keep thinking [C]of
It's not a [F]fancy place just a tavern in the [C]lonely part of town
Where [G7]lonely people find someone that [C]hopes to settle down
They tell [F]me to go and I can't under[C]stand
